  ('Bodyweight Single-Leg RDL Reach', 'bodyweight-single-leg-rdl-reach', 'Perform Bodyweight Single-Leg RDL Reach as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses bodyweight leverage to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 6, NULL, 90, 30, 'Single-leg hinge that builds posterior-chain strength with pelvis and balance control. Use it when the goal is force production, tissue capacity, and repeatable positions with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: hinge / posterior / chain / strength. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Bodyweight Single-Leg RDL Reach as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Set position first, control the hard range, then finish every rep like you could repeat it cleanly.', 'Single-leg hinge strength', 'capacity', 'hinge_posterior_chain_strength', 'single_leg_rdl_reach_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["single_leg_hip_hinge","pelvis_control","ankle_stability","trunk_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["hamstrings","glutes","foot_intrinsics","spinal_erectors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"single_leg","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Bodyweight Single-Leg RDL Reach uses bodyweight leverage to train single-leg hinge that builds posterior-chain strength with pelvis and balance control.","setup":["Have the athlete stand on one leg with a soft knee and reach the free leg long behind.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the first rep and rehearse the finish position."],