  ('Band Straight-Arm Pulldown', 'band-straight-arm-pulldown', 'Perform Band Straight-Arm Pulldown as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses band tension to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 10, NULL, 90, 50, 'Band-resisted straight-arm pulldown for lat strength and anti-extension trunk control. Use it when the goal is force production, tissue capacity, and repeatable positions with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: pull / hang / grip / strength. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Band Straight-Arm Pulldown as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Set position first, control the hard range, then finish every rep like you could repeat it cleanly.', 'Lat and trunk bracing strength', 'capacity', 'pull_hang_grip_strength', 'band_straight_arm_pulldown_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["shoulder_extension","scapular_depression","anti_extension_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["lats","teres_major","triceps_long_head","anterior_core"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Band Straight-Arm Pulldown uses band tension to train band-resisted straight-arm pulldown for lat strength and anti-extension trunk control.","setup":["Inspect the band for wear and set a secure anchor or foot position before the athlete loads it.","Have the athlete anchor a band overhead and stand tall with arms reaching slightly up toward the anchor.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brac