  ('Chin-Up Isometric Hold', 'chin-up-isometric-hold', 'Perform Chin-Up Isometric Hold as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses bodyweight leverage to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'INTERMEDIATE', 8, 3, NULL, 15, 60, 15, 'Top-position vertical pulling hold that builds grip, arm, and scapular strength. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: slow / eccentric / isometric / joint / resilience. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Chin-Up Isometric Hold as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Vertical pull isometric strength', 'resilience', 'slow_eccentric_isometric_joint_resilience', 'chin_up_isometric_hold_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["elbow_flexion_isometric","scapular_depression","grip_strength","trunk_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["lats","biceps","forearms","lower_trapezius"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Chin-Up Isometric Hold uses bodyweight leverage to train top-position vertical pulling hold that builds grip, arm, and scapular strength.","setup":["Confirm the bar, rings, or suspension point is stable and appropriate for the athlete''s bodyweight.","Have the athlete use a box or controlled jump to reach the top position with chin near or above bar.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete c