  ('Active Dead Hang', 'active-dead-hang', 'Perform Active Dead Hang as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses bodyweight leverage to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, NULL, 20, 60, 20, 'Active hang that builds grip strength, shoulder support, and scapular ownership. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: scapular / wrist / hand / support / resilience. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Active Dead Hang as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Hang and grip strength', 'resilience', 'scapular_wrist_hand_support_resilience', 'active_dead_hang_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["grip_support","scapular_depression","shoulder_flexion_tolerance","trunk_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["forearms","lats","lower_trapezius","rotator_cuff"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Active Dead Hang uses bodyweight leverage to train active hang that builds grip strength, shoulder support, and scapular ownership.","setup":["Confirm the bar, rings, or suspension point is stable and appropriate for the athlete''s bodyweight.","Have the athlete hang from a stable bar with hands secure and feet clear or lightly assisted.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the first rep an