  ('Bear Crawl Hold', 'bear-crawl-hold', 'Perform Bear Crawl Hold as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses bodyweight leverage to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, NULL, 20, 60, 20, 'Hovering quadruped hold that builds trunk stiffness, shoulder support, and hip control. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: trunk / pelvis / anti / movement / control. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Bear Crawl Hold as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Quadruped trunk strength', 'resilience', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'bear_crawl_hold_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["anti_rotation_bracing","shoulder_support","wrist_extension_load","hip_flexion_control"],"primary_tissues":["anterior_core","obliques","serratus_anterior","hip_flexors","forearms"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Bear Crawl Hold uses bodyweight leverage to train hovering quadruped hold that builds trunk stiffness, shoulder support, and hip control.","setup":["Have the athlete start on hands and knees with hands under shoulders and knees under hips.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the first rep and rehearse the finish position."],"execution_steps":["Begin from the organize