  ('Band Pallof Press', 'band-pallof-press', 'Perform Band Pallof Press as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses band tension to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 8, NULL, 60, 32, 'Standing band anti-rotation press that builds trunk stiffness against side-pull resistance. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: trunk / pelvis / anti / movement / control. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Band Pallof Press as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Anti-rotation trunk strength', 'resilience', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'band_pallof_press_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["anti_rotation_bracing","shoulder_horizontal_press","hip_stability"],"primary_tissues":["obliques","transverse_abdominis","glutes","serratus_anterior"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Band Pallof Press uses band tension to train standing band anti-rotation press that builds trunk stiffness against side-pull resistance.","setup":["Inspect the band for wear and set a secure anchor or foot position before the athlete loads it.","Have the athlete anchor a band at chest height and stand sideways to the anchor in an athletic stance.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the