  ('Band Anti-Rotation Walkout', 'band-anti-rotation-walkout', 'Perform Band Anti-Rotation Walkout as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses band tension to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 5, NULL, 60, 30, 'Side-step anti-rotation drill that builds trunk stiffness while the athlete moves away from band tension. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: trunk / pelvis / anti / movement / control. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Band Anti-Rotation Walkout as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Anti-rotation walkout strength', 'resilience', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'band_anti_rotation_walkout_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["anti_rotation_bracing","lateral_stepping_control","hip_stability"],"primary_tissues":["obliques","transverse_abdominis","glutes","adductors","foot_intrinsics"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Band Anti-Rotation Walkout uses band tension to train side-step anti-rotation drill that builds trunk stiffness while the athlete moves away from band tension.","setup":["Inspect the band for wear and set a secure anchor or foot position before the athlete loads it.","Have the athlete anchor a band at chest height, hold it at the sternum, and stand sideways to the ancho