  ('Band-Resisted Dead Bug Pullover', 'band-resisted-dead-bug-pullover', 'Perform Band-Resisted Dead Bug Pullover as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses band tension to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 6, NULL, 60, 30, 'Band-loaded dead bug that challenges trunk control as the arms pull against resistance. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: trunk / pelvis / anti / movement / control. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Band-Resisted Dead Bug Pullover as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Band-loaded dead bug strength', 'resilience', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'band_resisted_dead_bug_pullover_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["anti_extension_bracing","shoulder_flexion_extension_control","hip_flexion_control"],"primary_tissues":["anterior_core","lats","serratus_anterior","hip_flexors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Band-Resisted Dead Bug Pullover uses band tension to train band-loaded dead bug that challenges trunk control as the arms pull against resistance.","setup":["Inspect the band for wear and set a secure anchor or foot position before the athlete loads it.","Have the athlete lie on the back with a band anchored behind the head or held overhead and legs in tabletop."