  ('Tall-Kneeling Band Chop', 'tall-kneeling-band-chop', 'Perform Tall-Kneeling Band Chop as controlled resistance work. The athlete uses band tension to create a strength or control demand while keeping pain-free range, posture, and tempo repeatable.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 8, NULL, 60, 32, 'Tall-kneeling diagonal band chop that builds controlled rotation, anti-rotation braking, and trunk-hip linkage. Use it when the goal is position ownership, joint control, and tissue durability under low-to-moderate resistance with bands or body resistance rather than machines, free weights, or conditioning volume.', 'Primary subrole: trunk / pelvis / anti / movement / control. Score Strength and body-control transfer honestly. Use band tension, leverage, tempo, range, and rest to keep Tall-Kneeling Band Chop as resistance work. Do not turn it into a rushed conditioning station or over-tag it as explosiveness simply because the athlete is working hard.', 'Brace, breathe, and own the position. The rep ends when the shape changes.', 'Controlled rotational trunk strength', 'resilience', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'tall_kneeling_band_chop_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["controlled_trunk_rotation","anti_rotation_bracing","shoulder_diagonal_pull","hip_extension_control"],"primary_tissues":["obliques","transverse_abdominis","lats","glutes","serratus_anterior"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["alignment_control","tempo_control","bracing_under_resistance"],"postural_shape":"stacked_rib_pelvis","breathing_demand":"controlled","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Tall-Kneeling Band Chop uses band tension to train tall-kneeling diagonal band chop that builds controlled rotation, anti-rotation braking, and trunk-hip linkage.","setup":["Inspect the band for wear and set a secure anchor or foot position before the athlete loads it.","Have the athlete anchor a band high and kneel tall sideways or slightly 